"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-08-olympic-champion-dedicates-gold-dead-dog-my-whole-world-stopped-21386279\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Olympicgold medalist Sharon van Rouwendaal paid tribute to her late dog Rio after winning the women's marathon swimming inParis.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21, \"end\": 42, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharon_van_Rouwendaal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sharon van Rouwendaal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharon_van_Rouwendaal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharon_van_Rouwendaal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheDutchstar claimed the first gold medal of day 13 of the games on Thursday after a terrific swim in the River Seine.\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 236, \"end\": 247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Much has been made of the cleanliness - or lack thereof - of the Seine throughout the Olympics, but early in the morning 24 brave athletes took part in the 6.2 mile (10km) long race.\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 315, \"end\": 320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999944141109, \"rank\": 4.471058331342452e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics  This included Team GB's Leah Crisp who finished 20th, but with a time of 2 hours, 3 minutes and 34 seconds, gold went to Van Rouwendaal, ahead ofAustralia's Moesha Johnson andItaly's Ginevra Taddeucci.\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 521, \"end\": 528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.999978653221905, \"rank\": 1.0155504748918094e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 531, \"end\": 535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leah_Patterson-Baker\", \"score\": 0.9999717267037083, \"rank\": 2.796020638620734e-05, \"text\": \"Leah\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leah_Patterson-Baker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leah_Patterson-Baker\"}, {\"begin\": 536, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Crisp\", \"score\": 0.888693722023641, \"rank\": 0.12524626499716948, \"text\": \"Crisp\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Crisp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Crisp\"}, {\"begin\": 664, \"end\": 670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moesha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Moesha\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moesha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moesha\"}, {\"begin\": 671, \"end\": 678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Johnson\", \"score\": 0.9708828484702422, \"rank\": 0.026982461610576963, \"text\": \"Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Johnson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a deeply emotional victory for the 30-year-old, as she revealed post-race that her dog Rio, named after Rio de Janeiro where she also won gold in 2016, had passed shortly before the Paris games.\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 821, \"end\": 835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.268703603533135e-13, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998540261, \"rank\": 1.4586435739713257e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'In May, my little dog died,' she told reporters.\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 962, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'He needed an operation on his lungs so I gave it to him in hope that we could live after the Olympics together in my house and with my garden.\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 1107, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And he had complications after the surgery and he died.\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1163, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Then my world stopped and I did not care about swimming for like three weeks.\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was my little baby.\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1266, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'But my dad said that you have been away from him for like seven years because of competitions.\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1363, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do one more race and give it everything and swim for him.\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I got a tattoo [of his paw on her wrist] and thought \\\"let us try it\\\".\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I swam for him with my whole heart.\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1529, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I won it for him.'\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Van Rouwendaal's win was the Netherlands' 10th gold of Paris and with it they move to ninth in the medal table, with Team GB only just ahead in fifth on 12 golds at the time of writing.\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1735, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1579, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9966327534470252, \"rank\": 0.0026994587738015056, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 1605, \"end\": 1610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998540261, \"rank\": 1.4586435739713257e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.999978653221905, \"rank\": 1.0155504748918094e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1785, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Athlete sobs uncontrollably after suffering Olympic heartbreak moments before competing  ArrowMORE:The eye-watering sum Snoop Dogg is being paid for his Olympics coverage 'revealed'  ArrowMORE:Why USA star Raven Saunders is wearing a full face mask and glasses at the Olympics  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 2257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1989, \"end\": 1999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q